{\*\bkmkstart co_g_ID0EAJAE_1}{\*\bkmkend co_g_ID0EAJAE_1}
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
As for the consequences of invalidating the Solomon Amendment--another topic on which law professors might be expected to have an opinion--one would be that fewer students from elite law schools would be hired by the military because JAG recruiters wouldn\rquote t have the same access to those students as other recruiters would. Some of the discouraged students would be homosexual. Homosexuals as I have said are not excluded by the armed forces; they are forced to stay in the closet. (The situation was practically though not legally identical before \u8220\'3fdon\rquote t ask, don\rquote t tell.\u8221\'3f) Many homosexuals today are unwilling to remain closeted, but some are willing, even some who attend schools like Harvard and Yale. If they are recruited into a JAG corps, this may hasten the end of the formal ban on homosexuals. But what is more important, as Peter Berkowitz has pointed out, is that most students at such law schools, whatever their sexual orientation, are liberal.
}
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \i0 \fs16 
{\*\bkmkstart co_fnRef_F22332214522_ID0E1JAE_1}{\*\bkmkend co_fnRef_F22332214522_ID0E1JAE_1}
{\field {\*\fldinst HYPERLINK "#co_footnote_F22332214522_1" }{\fldrslt 
{\super \b0 \cf25 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs16 \sa0 \sb0 
22
}}}
}
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
 The more of them who are recruited for JAG service, the sooner the ban will collapse.
\par 
}
}
}
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
\u160\'3f
\par 
}
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \ri0 \i0 \qj \fs20 \li0 
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \ri0 \i0 \qj \fs20 \li0 
{\*\bkmkstart co_g_ID0EDKAE_1}{\*\bkmkend co_g_ID0EDKAE_1}
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
The practical causes and real-world consequences of the ban on homosexuals in the military, of the \u8220\'3fdon\rquote t ask, don\rquote t tell\u8221\'3f policy, and of the Solomon Amendment are the kind of sociopolitical facts that academics are in a better position to investigate than practicing 
}
{\b1 \cf1 \f2 \i0 \fs20 
{\*\bkmkstart co_pp_sp_100400_56_1}{\*\bkmkend co_pp_sp_100400_56_1}
{\b1 \cf1 \f2 \i0 \fs20 
{\b1 \cf1 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
*56
}
}
}
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
 lawyers are. Inquiring into those facts and presenting the results to the courts would be a more useful employment of law professors\rquote  time than hiring practitioners to flog precedents. There is a sheeplike character to all these professors signing on to a practitioner\rquote s brief (the sheep being led by the goat). One might have thought that some of these professors would speak in their own voice--express an individual view. Can\rquote t a law professor at Harvard or Yale write a brief? Well, maybe not any more; but he or she could do the research that only academics can do well, and let the practitioner convey the results in the brief. Do these professors perhaps not care about the issue strongly enough to actually work on it? Do they want more than to show that their heart is in the right place, or at least in the same place as their students\rquote  hearts?
\par 
}
}
}
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
\u160\'3f
\par 
}
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \ri0 \i0 \qj \fs20 \li0 
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \ri0 \i0 \qj \fs20 \li0 
{\*\bkmkstart co_g_ID0EJLAE_1}{\*\bkmkend co_g_ID0EJLAE_1}
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
But Rosenkranz is on to something, though not to what he thinks he\rquote s on to, when he says that \u8220\'3flaw schools are more than just vocational schools that teach students to draft briefs and close deals. Law schools are, and define themselves as, normative institutions. They aspire to shape future lawyers who \u8216\'3fcan profoundly change our society, its mores and values,\u8217\'3f and who will urge their visions of justice on society at large. Law schools admonish their students that \u8216\'3fissues of justice are at the core of [their] missions,\u8217\'3f and urge students \u8216\'3fto accept the challenge of more clearly defining a just system.\u8221\'3f\u8217\'3f
}
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \i0 \fs16 
{\*\bkmkstart co_fnRef_F23332214522_ID0E5MAE_1}{\*\bkmkend co_fnRef_F23332214522_ID0E5MAE_1}
{\field {\*\fldinst HYPERLINK "#co_footnote_F23332214522_1" }{\fldrslt 
{\super \b0 \cf25 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs16 \sa0 \sb0 
23
}}}
}
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
 Soaring rhetoric, but inaccurate. American law schools are professional schools, not secular 
}
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \i1 \fs20 
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i1 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
madrasahs
}
}
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
, and they spend a lot more time teaching their students how to defend society\rquote s \u8220\'3fmores and values\u8221\'3f than how to challenge them. The vast majority of the students at the elite law schools become corporate lawyers and defend the mores and values of giant corporations. Revolutionaries they are not. Rosenkranz\rquote s brief invokes a selected subset of American mores and values in defense of his constitutional claim.
\par 
}
}
}
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
\u160\'3f
\par 
}
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \ri0 \i0 \qj \fs20 \li0 
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \ri0 \i0 \qj \fs20 \li0 
{\*\bkmkstart co_g_ID0EVNAE_1}{\*\bkmkend co_g_ID0EVNAE_1}
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
What is particularly revealing about the passage I\rquote ve just quoted is the uncritical assumption that legal education has a liberal agenda, specifically a liberal agenda in which homosexual rights occupy a high place. 
}
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
The Solomon Amendment must go 
}
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \i1 \fs20 
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i1 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
because
}
}
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
 law schools are normative institutions. Rosenkranz invokes \u8220\'3fvisions of justice\u8221\'3f (plural) but does not acknowledge the possibility that there is a military vision of justice that challenges justice as homosexual rights. 
}
{\b1 \cf1 \f2 \i0 \fs20 
{\*\bkmkstart co_pp_sp_100400_57_1}{\*\bkmkend co_pp_sp_100400_57_1}
{\b1 \cf1 \f2 \i0 \fs20 
{\b1 \cf1 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
*57
}
}
}
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
 So comfortable are Rosenkranz and the legal professoriat with that agenda that it does not occur to him or to it to inquire into the practical dimensions of JAG recruiting at elite law schools, including the possibility that by discouraging military recruiters the schools are helping to perpetuate a conservative military culture; JAG recruiters are surely welcome at Ave Maria.
\par 
}
}
}
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
\u160\'3f
\par 
}
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \ri0 \i0 \qj \fs20 \li0 
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \ri0 \i0 \qj \fs20 \li0 
{\*\bkmkstart co_g_ID0EOOAE_1}{\*\bkmkend co_g_ID0EOOAE_1}
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
The left-liberal domination of elite law school faculties
}
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \i0 \fs16 
{\*\bkmkstart co_fnRef_F24332214522_ID0EUOAE_1}{\*\bkmkend co_fnRef_F24332214522_ID0EUOAE_1}
{\field {\*\fldinst HYPERLINK "#co_footnote_F24332214522_1" }{\fldrslt 
{\super \b0 \cf25 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs16 \sa0 \sb0 
24
}}}
}
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
 has had the debilitating effect on the intellect that John Stuart Mill in 
}
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \i1 \fs20 
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i1 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
On Liberty
}
}
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
 assigned to the groupthink of his day.
}
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \i0 \fs16 
{\*\bkmkstart co_fnRef_F25332214522_ID0E2OAE_1}{\*\bkmkend co_fnRef_F25332214522_ID0E2OAE_1}
{\field {\*\fldinst HYPERLINK "#co_footnote_F25332214522_1" }{\fldrslt 
{\super \b0 \cf25 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs16 \sa0 \sb0 
25
}}}
}
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
 When you inhabit a cozy burrow of like thinkers, your ideas are not challenged and they grow flabby. They become unexamined habits of mind--articles of faith that when finally challenged provoke anger rather than reasoned response because the ability to reason about them has atrophied. Missing from the professors\rquote  briefs is an awareness that there are two sides to the issue of the right of homosexuals to full equality in the armed forces and that law professors could contribute more to a sound resolution by dispassionate study than by signing their names to conventional briefs written by practicing lawyers.
}
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \i0 \fs16 
{\*\bkmkstart co_fnRef_F26332214522_ID0EGPAE_1}{\*\bkmkend co_fnRef_F26332214522_ID0EGPAE_1}
{\field {\*\fldinst HYPERLINK "#co_footnote_F26332214522_1" }{\fldrslt 
{\super \b0 \cf25 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs16 \sa0 \sb0 
26
}}}
}
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
 Even a sense of irony withers in an atmosphere of intellectual conformity. Law professors should be \u8220\'3freluctant to promiscuously hurl accusations of discrimination at the military, especially since many of the law professors had only a few years ago argued for, and won from the Supreme Court in 
}
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \i1 \fs20 
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i1 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
Grutter v Bollinger
}
}
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
 (2003), a special exemption to classify at their law schools on the basis of race because of their presumed special expertise concerning the need in legal education for diverse student bodies.\u8221\'3f
}
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \i0 \fs16 
{\*\bkmkstart co_fnRef_F27332214522_ID0EZPAE_1}{\*\bkmkend co_fnRef_F27332214522_ID0EZPAE_1}
{\field {\*\fldinst HYPERLINK "#co_footnote_F27332214522_1" }{\fldrslt 
{\super \b0 \cf25 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs16 \sa0 \sb0 
27
}}}
}
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
 The military has its needs as well, and perhaps even some expertise.
\par 
}
}
}
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
\u160\'3f
\par 
}
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \ri0 \i0 \qj \fs20 \li0 
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \ri0 \i0 \qj \fs20 \li0 
{\*\bkmkstart co_g_ID0ECQAE_1}{\*\bkmkend co_g_ID0ECQAE_1}
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
Judges sense a growing chasm between the professoriat and the judiciary. In 
}
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \i1 \fs20 
